{
  "texts": [
    "This is similarly a binary multi-label classification problem where anywhere from 0-7 frame elements may be present in a tweet.",
    "Model Setup.",
    "For each of these four classification problems, our goal is to train computational models to predict the appropriate labels.",
    "We use a common approach in NLP,",
    "where we build our classifiers on top of RoBERTa (Liu et al., 2019b), a highly-parameterized pretrained language model, which has been trained on vast amounts of unlabeled data."
  ]
}